                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.0145/8.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 186.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I acknowledge the receipt of Ambassador
                    Rockhill’s despatch No. 592, of June 21, in further reference to the policy of
                    the Russian Government to extend to twelve miles the limits of Russian
                    territorial waters. Careful note has been made of your statements as to the
                    steps already taken in this direction.</p>
                <p>The Embassy is requested to keep the Department informed of future developments
                    in this matter.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
